{
  "texts": [
    "These span concrete objects, natural phenomena, and fantastical entities.Trial Structure.",
    "For each test concept, we run:• Control trial: No injection (α = 0).",
    "Model should report no detection.• Injection trials: Injection at α ∈ {40, 60, 80, 100}.",
    "Model should detect and identify.Metrics.",
    "We report:• True Positive Rate (TPR): Fraction of injection trials where the model correctly detects and identifies the concept.• False Positive Rate (FPR): Fraction of control trials where the model claims detection.• Detection Rate: Fraction of injection trials where the model claims any detection (regardless of identification accuracy).• Identification Rate: Among detected trials, fraction where the correct concept is named.Scoring."
  ]
}